{"TopicId":196420,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Kerbals constantly sliding, in even terrain too","CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-20T10:10:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-20T10:10:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was doing some Kerbin ground science when i noticed my Kerbals were sliding i guess kinda fast, in a full even terrain,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMun and Minmus is same too but a lot slower.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut on Kerbin, they sliding fast, havent even tested in in uneven terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-20T10:21:20Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2020 10:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T17:02:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/9557\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/9557\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/13413\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/13413\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery old problem which is being attributed to the Unity/PhysX engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the other hand some mods appear to find ways to work around it to more or less degree (and so far none of them apply to kerbals - yet):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8404329404\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/180083-ksp-110x-parking-brake-030-2020-07-20/page/2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T17:22:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841737\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598029364\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/9557\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/9557\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/13413\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/13413\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery old problem which is being attributed to the Unity/PhysX engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the other hand some mods appear to find ways to work around it to more or less degree (and so far none of them apply to kerbals - yet):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know but lately there is a huge improvement and i have rarely seen\u00A0any vessels/crafts sliding,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot to mention if you use structural panels and or grippads.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts been so much better in the latest versions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats why i was surprised to see Kerbals still follow the old sliding habits, but hey, my bases/crafts/planes etc rarely slide, maybe not even at all so i am ok, just weird to see the Kerbal thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-21T17:23:09Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2020 05:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T17:27:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841737\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598029364\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/9557\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/9557\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/13413\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/13413\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery old problem which is being attributed to the Unity/PhysX engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the other hand some mods appear to find ways to work around it to more or less degree (and so far none of them apply to kerbals - yet):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4999074748\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/180083-ksp-110x-parking-brake-030-2020-07-20/page/2/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s much better than it was before version 1.10, so I though, that my mod will be in decline, but I can try to apply it to Kerbals. After all, BonVoyage will include Kerbals in the next update too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-21T17:38:38Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2020 05:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by maja\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T17:31:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841757\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598030856\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s much better than it was before version 1.10, so I though, that my mod will be in decline, but I can try it to apply to Kerbals. After all, BonVoyage will include Kerbals in the next update too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be honest, i just flew some of my crafts in Kerbin and they slide a LOT lol, i didnt realize things were so bad.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOmg they are sliding so much i cant use Scanning Arm on Kerbin!It says Vessel moved!Scan aborted!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-21T17:42:22Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2020 05:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T17:54:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/168379-maja/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022168379\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/168379-maja/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@maja\u003C/a\u003EThank you Sir, downloaded mod, loaded up game, no sliding, Scanning arm just fine...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152460\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152460-swjr-swis/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@swjr-swis\u003C/a\u003EThank you for pointing out this mod, i didnt realize how much sliding annoys me until i found out how it is not to slide \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T17:58:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841737\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598029364\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the other hand some mods appear to find ways to work around it to more or less degree (and so far none of them apply to kerbals - yet)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does not work for Kerbals (tested right know)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-21T18:05:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223841786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598032692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does not work for Kerbals (tested right know)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be nice if that was something doable but i am happy my vessels dont slide anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit number 3, they seem to slide if on top of the vessel or on the ladder,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut personally i am just happy my vessels dont slide.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-21T18:12:10Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2020 06:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansAcker","CreatedById":195534,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-22T12:39:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m going to give \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E\u0027 Driftless a try. It doesn\u0027t really do much, \u0022just\u0022 zeroing out the torque:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/net-lisias-ksp/KSP-Recall/blob/master/Source/Driftless/PartModule.cs#L106\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/net-lisias-ksp/KSP-Recall/blob/master/Source/Driftless/PartModule.cs#L106\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5624210116\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179030-ksp-141-tweakscale-under-lisias-management-24321-2020-00804/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3841521\u0026amp;embedComment=3841521\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:299px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-22T15:53:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223842173\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196420\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221598099987\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022195534\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HansAcker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, HansAcker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022just\u0022 zeroing out the torque:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI been using Parking Brake mod since yesterday and i have no problems at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe vessels are anchored, nothing is sliding,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nofcourse i might have missed something but so far it does a perfect job.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo more constant sliding for me\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-22T15:54:35Z\u0022 title=\u002208/22/2020 03:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 22, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-27T20:48:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u002